text: Leksan Leksands IF is an ice hockey club in Leksand in Sweden. It was established in 1919. The club adopted the game of ice hockey in 1938. It won the Swedish national championship in 1969, 1973, 1974 and 1975. It lost the Swedish national finals in 1959, 1964, 1971, 1972, 1975 and 1989. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official website Category:1919 establishments in Sweden Category:Ice hockey teams in Sweden
